    "In the following equations, an upper index refers to the layer number while column vectors, denoted in boldface, refer to all neurons in a given layer.",
    "The D real-valued inputs, such as pixel intensities, are first scaled to the interval [0, 1], resulting in the vector x ð0Þ = ðx ð0Þ 1, x ð0Þ 2,.",
    ", x ð0Þ D Þ T where x ð0Þ j 2 ½0, 1, and then encoded into spiking times of the SNN input layer using TTFS coding (Fig. 1b).",
    "A high input pixel intensity leads to an early spike at time t ð0Þ j = t ð0Þ max À τ c x ð0Þ j, and specifically for x ð0Þ j = 0 no spike will be emitted.",
    "The conversion parameter τ c translates unit-free inputs into time units."
